transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Good morning, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yes, I just got noticed Saturday that you did a transaction that I was unaware of, a prescription that I do not want.

Speaker 1: I want to make sure you cancel it.

Speaker 2: Okay, let me take a look for you.

Speaker 1: Mr. Duke French in Las Vegas, Nevada?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Yes, so I see that you have, with Scoreblue, you have a VIP account for Viagra 100mg 40 tablet.

Speaker 2: I think what happened was, based on your original prescription, you were up for a refill.

Speaker 1: But if you don't need a refill, what you can do, I can advise the pharmacy for you to pause the prescription.

Speaker 2: So that way, you just can order as needed.

Speaker 1: Instead of getting 40 pills every other month, you can order as needed, and you can change the quantity as well.

Speaker 2: If that's a lot, you can get 25, you can get 10, but not get any every month or every other month.

Speaker 1: They pause you, I think, up to half a year, and you can just reorder.

Speaker 2: So you don't get it on a monthly anymore.

Speaker 1: I want to cancel totally.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Alright, let me do that for you.

Speaker 2: And stop that transaction.

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 2: Let's see.

Speaker 1: Alright, so I'm going to cancel the doctor prescription and the account.

Speaker 2: So that being said, if something changes in the future, just keep in mind that, you know,

Speaker 1: you're probably going to have a different price because they're going to have to get you a new one.

Speaker 2: They're going to have to refinance a new doctor to evaluate your profile to provide the medicine.

Speaker 1: That's fine. Reverse that charge too.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let me...

Speaker 2: Let me...

Speaker 1: Alright, I was able to successfully reverse the transaction because it wasn't fully processed.

Speaker 2: I think it happened on Saturday.

Speaker 1: And then I'll cancel the account and do the prescription for you.

Speaker 2: So you're all set, okay?

Speaker 1: So look up at Corporate Business Day, you will see the refund.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you're welcome.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
